response.overview: He will always be remembered as the vigorous president who inspired America, a charismatic leader who gave the nation a sense of pride and confidence. John Fitzgerald Kennedy was different from any other president America had ever had. His sharp mind, quick insight, and unlimited determination earned him friends, confidants, and devoted followers. As a World War II hero, respected senator, author of Why England Slept, and Pulitzer Prize winner, Kennedy viewed life as a race against boredom. The crucial moments of his life and presidency are revisited here through archival footage and interviews with famous journalists, Hollywood actors, and White House members. Explore the irresistible story of this unforgettable leader and the dynasty he left behind.
response.title: Biography: John F. Kennedy
